cional</a>,  e  <a href=\"https://www.rnp.br/\">Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa</a>) to provide support for the participation of Brazilian scientists in large international programs requiring an IT infrastructure such as SDSS, DES, DESI and LSST. Some of its main projects include:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Reduce pipeline available at CTIO to assess the quality of the images gathered by DECam; </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Science Portal, a comprehensive integrated web-based end-to-end system to streamline the production of ancillary information used to create value-added science ready catalog to feed a variety of science analysis workflows;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Data Server interface available at Fermilab since April 2014 to enable the visualization of images and objects, and to carry out queries in the DESDM database. The interface has been accessed 4500 times over the past three years by 250 users;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Look Framework (QLF) being developed to assess the quality of the 15,000 spectra of the 5,000 objects to be observed in each exposure of DESI.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server being made available at NCSA and which will be used as one of the interfaces of the DES data release DR1.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, LIneA maintains a data center (1000 cores processing cluster, 1 PB mass storage and a host of other machines) for its affiliates, currently around 80 members, a mirror site for SDSS providing independent SkyServer and CasJobs services, and provides support to the computer infrastructure being used by the APOGEE-2 project at the Las Campanas Observatory.</span>','About us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2017-12-11 10:15:05','2017-12-11 12:15:05','',0,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home//?page_id=92',0,'page','',0),(222,1,'2017-12-11 10:15:05','2017-12-11 12:15:05','<b><i>About LIneA</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Laboratório Interinstitucional de e-Astronomia (LIneA) was created in November 2010 by an agreement signed by three research institutes of the Ministry of Science, Technology, Innovation and Communication (<a href=\"http://www.mctic.gov.br/\">MCTIC</a>) (<a href=\"http://www.lncc.br/\">Laboratório Nacional de Computação Científica</a>, <a href=\"http://on.br/\">Observatório Nacional</a>,  e  <a href=\"https://www.rnp.br/\">Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa</a>) to provide support for the participation of Brazilian scientists in large international programs requiring an IT infrastructure such as SDSS, DES, DESI and LSST. Some of its main projects include:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Reduce pipeline available at CTIO to assess the quality of the images gathered by DECam; </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Science Portal, a comprehensive integrated web-based end-to-end system to streamline the production of ancillary information used to create value-added science ready catalog to feed a variety of science analysis workflows;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Data Server interface available at Fermilab since April 2014 to enable the visualization of images and objects, and to carry out queries in the DESDM database. The interface has been accessed 4500 times over the past three years by 250 users;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Look Framework (QLF) being developed to assess the quality of the 15,000 spectra of the 5,000 objects to be observed in each exposure of DESI.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server being made available at NCSA and which will be used as one of the interfaces of the DES data release DR1.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, LIneA maintains a data center (1000 cores processing cluster, 1 PB mass storage and a host of other machines) for its affiliates, currently around 80 members, a mirror site for SDSS providing independent SkyServer and CasJobs services, and provides support to the computer infrastructure being used by the APOGEE-2 project at the Las Campanas Observatory.</span>','About us','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2017-12-11 10:15:05','2017-12-11 12:15:05','',92,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(193,1,'2017-11-13 16:10:32','2017-11-13 18:10:32','<b><i>About LIneA</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Laboratório Interinstitucional de e-Astronomia (LIneA) was created in November 2010 by an agreement signed by three research institutes of the Ministry of Science, Technology, Innovation and Communication (<a href=\"http://www.mctic.gov.br/\">MCTIC</a>) (<a href=\"http://www.lncc.br/\">Laboratório Nacional de Computação Científica</a>, <a href=\"http://on.br/\">Observatório Nacional</a>,  e  <a href=\"https://www.rnp.br/\">Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa</a>) to provide support for the participation of Brazilian scientists in large international programs requiring an IT infrastructure such as SDSS, DES, DESI and LSST. Some of its main projects include:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Reduce pipeline available at CTIO to assess the quality of the images gathered by DECam; </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Science Portal, a comprehensive integrated web-based end-to-end system to streamline the production of ancillary information used to create value-added science ready catalog to feed a variety of science analysis workflows;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Data Server interface available at Fermilab since April 2014 to enable the visualization of images and objects, and to carry out queries in the DESDM database. The interface has been accessed 4500 times over the past three years by 250 users;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Look Framework (QLF) being developed to assess the quality of the 15,000 spectra of the 5,000 objects to be observed in each exposure of DESI.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server being made available at NCSA and which will be used as one of the interfaces of the DES data release DR1.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, LIneA maintains a data center (1000 cores processing cluster, 1 PB mass storage and a host of other machines) for its affiliates, currently around 80 members, a mirror site for SDSS providing independent SkyServer and CasJobs services, and provides support to the computer infrastructure being used by the APOGEE-2 project at the Las Campanas Observatory.</span>\r\n\r\n<b><i>About the LIneA Science Server Interface</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Currently the LIneA Science Server provides access to the following services:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky viewer: display a panoramic view of DES images across its footprint.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Target viewer: visualize and manage list of objects. One can rank,  reject entries filter by properties, and create mosaics.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Science products: browse scientific products produce by LIneA Science portal or DES collaboration, such as maps, VACs, and cluster catalogs.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the future we expect it to also provide</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User query: write SQL queries in a web interface to get information from DES NCSA database.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Catalog builder: build a catalog using the framework presented in Fausti et al.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b><i>Credits</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We would like to thank the contribution of the following people and organizations:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NCSA team for providing the infrastructure and tools such as which are use by Science Server </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">E. Bertin for the use of  VisiOmatic and for helping in its installation</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">P. Fernique for helping in the integration of Aladin in the Science Server framework</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA team:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Luiz Nicolaci da Costa (Lead Scientist)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Angelo Fausti Neto (Technical Lead)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Glauber Costa</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riccardo Campisano</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rafael Brito</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fabio Oliveira</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Felipe Machado </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ricardo Ogando</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guilherme Soares</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cida Silveira</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maria Luiza Sanchez</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Humberto Aranha</span></li>\r\n</ul>','About us','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2017-11-13 16:10:32','2017-11-13 18:10:32','',92,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(93,1,'2017-08-21 15:50:03','2017-08-21 18:50:03','In Construction.','About US','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2017-08-21 15:50:03','2017-08-21 18:50:03','',92,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home//92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(84,1,'2017-08-10 16:04:00','2017-08-10 19:04:00','[si-contact-form form=\'1\']','Contact us','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-us','','','2017-09-15 17:40:13','2017-09-15 20:40:13','',0,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home//?page_id=84',0,'page','',0),(85,1,'2017-08-10 16:04:00','2017-08-10 19:04:00','','Contact US','','inherit','closed','closed','','84-revision-v1','','','2017-08-10 16:04:00','2017-08-10 19:04:00','',84,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home//84-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(38,1,'2017-06-07 17:40:31','2017-06-07 20:40:31','','cutout_200x200','','inherit','open','closed','','cutout_200x200','','','2017-06-07 17:40:31','2017-06-07 20:40:31','',0,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home//wp-content/uploads/2017/06/cutout_200x200.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(170,1,'2017-10-11 15:52:46','