 DES footprint for a given release using Aladin where DES images and systematic maps can be displayed. User can also dive into a tile image and examine it using VisiOmatic. At the tile level, images from different data releases (if available at that particular tile) can be compared side by side to perform quality assessment. Both Aladin and VisiOmatic have their native tools available, as well as complementary ones. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>At footprint level (Aladin) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Examine DES images in the footprint as well as related maps (ex. systematics). Use left menu to select what will be displayed, example: tiles, footprint, and layers. You can double-click a tile or center at a given position using the top right form, and click Go to examine tile.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>At tile level (VisiOmatic) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Compare images from different releases. Lock position, so both screens show same regions of the sky as you move around. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overlay catalogs from DES and other surveys.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Change image levels to improve contrast. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Available Videos</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Sky Viewer adjustments</li>\r\n 	<li>Sky Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"2\"]','Sky Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/sky/','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 10:00:04','2017-09-18 13:00:04','',6,'https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(105,1,'2017-08-25 11:51:50','2017-08-25 14:51:50','<h2>Improvements</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>improvement with big text to test the space at sidebar</li>\r\n 	<li>improvement</li>\r\n 	<li>improvement</li>\r\n 	<li>improvement</li>\r\n 	<li>improvement with big text to test the space at sidebar</li>\r\n 	<li>improvement with big text to test the space at sidebar</li>\r\n 	<li>imp